TALK SHOW

By:
EDITED BY LARRY LIGHT, WITH PAUL ENG

``The world is full of people whose notion of a satisfactory future is, in
fact, a return to an idealized past.''
-- Robertson Davies, the Canadian author of The Cunning Man, who died at 82
on Dec. 2

