January 8, 1996   Number 3457

STEVE JOBS

How sweet it is. STEVE JOBS, co-founder of Apple Computer, has been trying
to come up with a second hit for a decade. No such luck--until Nov. 29.
That's when his company, Pixar Animation Studios, makers of the smash hit
movie Toy Story, went public with a bang. The stock, priced at 22, zoomed
to 49 before falling back to 24. Jobs's 80% stake was briefly worth $1.1
billion. What's next? His other company, NeXT, is making Web software, and
Jobs may see his third IPO in early 1996.

