CALLING CORPORATE AMERICA'S BLUFF

By:
EDITED BY THANE PETERSON

IN THE MAYBE-IT-DOESN'T-PAY to-stick-your-neck-out category: House Minority
Leader Richard A. Gephardt and 45 fellow Democrats are challenging more
than 90 executives to detail business tax breaks they would be willing to
sacrifice to help balance the federal budget. The challenge, in letters
mailed Dec. 22, was prompted by national newspaper ads signed by the
business leaders imploring Congress to put ``everything on the table'' to
reach a budget deal. Among others, the letter went to Paul Allaire of
