ET CETERA...

By:
EDITED BY THANE PETERSON

-- The Feds and Occidental Chemical settled the 16-year-old Love Canal
cleanup case.
-- Cordis shares fell after Johnson & Johnson extended its review of its
buyout offer.
-- Daiwa's ex-N.Y. general manager was indicted for allegedly helping hide
losses.
-- Goldman Sachs is mulling whether to dissolve its partnership and go
public.

